      <h1 class='title'>BETHLEM HOSPITAL.</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='house-of-lords-report' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'> Deb 28 April 1925 vol 60 c1087</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1087' title='Col. 1087 &mdash;  Deb 28 April 1925 vol 60 c1087' name='column_1087' href='#column_1087' rel='bookmark'>1087</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0060P0-02806'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0060P0_19250428_HOLR2_2' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Petition of the Mayor and Commonalty and citizens of the City of London, the Masters, Guardians, and Governors of the House and Hospital called Bethlem, praying lor leave to introduce a Bill to provide for the removal of Bethlem Hospital to the Monks Orchard Estate at Addington in Surrey, and Beckenham and West Wickham in Kent, and for the disposal of the existing hospital premises and convalescent home, and for other purposes, together with a copy of the proposed Bill annexed thereto; read, and referred to the Examiners.
      </p>
